metadata.name: Amnesia
metadata.description:
amnesia
/amˈniːzɪə/

noun
a partial or total loss of memory.

A fashion narrative that uses the idea of being imprisoned in a dream to convey the feeling of being enclosed in a cocoon. 

I hold fast in my conviction and hope, yet I can't say that I have very distinct memories of you. I feel entrapped and really cold because the gold chains aren't actually gold. We might have shared few good memories together, but I'm a slave with memories as brittle as a feather.
